{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b03fd659-ca70-4661-a176-e07d4c28e81b","content":"No files found in the current directory. Since there's no existing file to modify, here's exactly what you need:\n\n### 1. Add `x:DataType` to your XAML\n\nOn your `ContentPage` root element, add the `x:DataType` attribute pointing to your ViewModel:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" FontSize=\"{Binding FontSize}\" />\n\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n\n        <Slider Minimum=\"10\" Maximum=\"36\"\n                Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" />\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nReplace `YourApp.ViewModels` with your actual namespace.\n\n### 2. Catch binding errors at build time\n\nCompiled bindings are **validated at compile time by default** once `x:DataType` is set — any typo like `{Binding Themee}` becomes a **build error**, not a silent runtime failure.\n\nTo ensure this is enforced project-wide, add to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n    <!-- Treat binding failures as build errors (default for new projects) -->\n    <MauiStrictXamlCompilation>true</MauiStrictXamlCompilation>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n### Key rules\n\n- **Every `x:DataType` scope is checked.** If a child element has a different `BindingContext`, set a new `x:DataType` on that element.\n- **To opt out for one binding** (e.g., binding to the page itself), use `x:DataType=\"\"` locally or the `{Binding Source=...}` pattern.\n- **Build output** will show errors like:\n  ```\n  XC0045: Binding: Property \"Themee\" not found on \"SettingsViewModel\"\n  ```\n\nThat's all — adding `x:DataType` is the only XAML change needed. The compiler does the rest.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1f2ff8aa-8b88-4657-be49-65bd90f2b3e8","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"No files found. The user is describing a page they have but it's not in the current working directory. Let me check what's in the current directory.","outputTokens":625},"id":"3099dd3d-aa5d-4c34-b769-a546739b7d90","timestamp":"2026-04-03T01:20:37.467Z","parentId":"81dbdf5b-783f-45a5-bd63-ea5c45f4376b"}
